<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/55317248-thomas-dachsel"><img alt="" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/m_100x100-c7bfe730633c9983e27caaa66a8e244a.png" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/55317248-thomas-dachsel">Thomas Dachsel</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">With this book, there are various layers of realization, somehow mirrored by the protagonist writing several revisions of his autobiography, claiming <a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">With this book, there are various layers of realization, somehow mirrored by the protagonist writing several revisions of his autobiography, claiming that each iteration would be closer to the truth.<br /><br />Of course in reality there is no city by the name Jethra, but there is a city by name of London, so the first perspective is definitely closer to reality.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
